The paper deals with the analysis of the diameter of hyperbolic random graphs, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The use of network algorithms and the analysis of their behavior suggest a connection to computer science and information theory (cs.IT). The study of hyperbolic random graphs is also relevant to the field of network science (cs.NE) and social networks (cs.SI).
